  "prompt": "It goes without saying that money laundering is illegal, doesn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, absolutely. Money laundering is indeed illegal in virtually all jurisdictions around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or other criminal acts) appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. \n\nGovernments and international organizations, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), have established stringent laws and regulations to combat money laundering. Penalties for engaging in or facilitating money laundering can be severe, including hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment. Financial institutions and other businesses are also required to implement anti-money laundering (AML) measures to detect and report suspicious activities.",
